The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | PM hotline to Beijing 
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      PM hotline to Beijing 
                            
	Beijing, April 7 (PTI): India and China today signed an agreement for a hotline between their Prime Ministers, New Delhis first such direct telephone facility in recent years with the head of any country.        
	Foreign minister S.M. Krishna and his Chinese counterpart Yang Jiechi signed the pact here after talks that also touched on Indias objections to Beijings issue of stapled visas to Indians from Jammu and Kashmir.         
	Dedicated phone lines will be set up for Manmohan Singh and his Chinese counterpart Wen Jiabao to hold direct conversations whenever they want.                                                                                                                                                           
